@page "/cookies"

<div class="legal-page">
    <h1>Cookies Policy</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: August 29, 2025</em></p>
    <p>This Cookies Policy explains what cookies are, how we use them, and your choices regarding cookies when you use our website and services.</p>

    <h2>What Are Cookies?</h2>
    <p>Cookies are small text files that are stored on your device (computer, smartphone, tablet) when you visit a website. They help websites recognize your device and improve your browsing experience.</p>

    <h2>How We Use Cookies</h2>
    <p>We use cookies to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Ensure the proper functionality of our website.</li>
        <li>Remember your preferences (such as language or login).</li>
        <li>Enable secure payments through Stripe.</li>
        <li>Analyze traffic and improve performance of our services.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
    <p><strong>Essential Cookies</strong>: Required for the operation of our website (e.g., for booking scooters)</p>
    <p><strong>Preformance Cookies</strong>: Help us understand how visitors use our website, so we can improve it.</p>
    <p><strong>Functional Cookies</strong>: Remember your preferences to provide a personalized experience.</p>
    <p><strong>Third-Party Cookies</strong>: Some third-party services we use (such as Stripe for payments, Google Maps for location) may set their own cookies.</p>

    <h2>Your Choices</h2>
    <p>When you visit our website, you will be asked to accept or manage cookies. You can:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Accept all cookies</li>
        <li>Manage preferences to allow only certain types of cookies.</li>
        <li>Disable cookies through your browser settings (note: some features may not function properly if you do this).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>More Information</h2>
    <p>For more details on how we process personal data, please read our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>
</div>
